item.title: CVE-2022-1847|2024-08-03T00:17:00.404Z -- unknown -- rotating%20posts
item.description: The Rotating Posts WordPress plugin through 1.11 does not have CSRF check in place when updating its settings, which could allow attackers to make a logged in admin change them via a CSRF attack
